{
  "__comment": [
    "Variant spelling mappings for search. Both indexed text and search",
    "queries are normalised through this table, so a search for either",
    "form finds both. Keys and values are single normalised tokens:",
    "lower-case, accents stripped, ae/oe ligatures expanded, apostrophes",
    "removed (so \"tho'\" appears here as \"tho\"). Add entries freely.",
    "Normalisation Porter-stems after this table, so inflected forms no",
    "longer need their own rows (a base \"shew\" -> \"show\" also catches",
    "shews/shewn); the existing inflected rows are kept but redundant.",
    "Map an old spelling to its modern spelling, not to its stem."
  ],
